<br>
I suggest dropping the &quot;turning into demon&quot; variant, but still make it a nasty plague... perhaps something with a long incubation period and contagious phase, but a short and very painful period with symptoms, ending in death.  Make it a &quot;corona&quot; virus like influenza, the common cold, and SARS, and you have something that would be very difficult - if not impossible - to cure.  <br>
<br>
One small point, though: diseases tend to stick to a certain host species and don't spread to others unless it can find a new host that's &quot;tasty&quot;.  If your galactic civilization is a multi-species variety, then chances are this plague will affect only one of the many species - which could, in turn, cause new conflicts.  A blockade might not be necessary, though getting help for one species out of perhaps hundreds might prove difficult (this occurs even today - look at Africa.  AIDS is spreading unchecked through many central African countries, but efforts to make anti-AIDS drugs available to these countries, or to provide funding for African hospitals and doctors, constantly fall short because governments and people elsewhere prefer to close their eyes to the suffering).  <br>
<br>
You've got a good seed concept for a story here.  Keep exploring it, and see where it takes you.<br>
<br>
