<br>
I have been thinking about this story since the idea first popped into my mind, and I have expanded on it a bit. The main character still doesn't have a name but I'll just keep calling him Duo until I get one.<br>
<br>
Anyway, In the beginning of the story, Duo is sent to jail, but why? I was thinking that maybe Duo could be sent to jail because he was found guilty of murder. The man that Duo murdered is a member of a terrorist organzation which intends to release a deadly virus onto Duo's home planet. Yet because there was no evidence to support this, Duo is sent to Prison.<br>
<br>
While Duo is away, he learns that the terrorist organization succeeds in their plan. So Duo hopes to escape from prison to help his family. Duo's inmate wishes to help Duo in his quest as long as Duo can help him escape prison as well. Duo agrees.<br>
<br>
The two succeed in escaping from prison, but unknown to Duo, his inmate is actualy a member of the terrorist organization which released the virus in the first place.<br>
<br>
I also never considered using a multi-racial galaxy, only humans. I have also scratched the idea of having the virus turn the infected into demons, way too unoriginal.<br>
<br>
Please keep the critiques comming!<br>
